But the Trump administration has other matters at hand, namely the case of Roger Stone's conviction.
Trump tweeted support for his former adviser while Attorney General Bill Barr recommended a lighter sentence than the one prosecutors asked for.
It turns out Barr was right once again, and Stone received a 40-month sentence after a judge decided prosecutors were out of line.
